"id":"12764"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15755"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32918"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102753","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102753"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old Aboriginal woman presents to the General Practice clinic with her two children, aged 4 and 6 years. She reports feeling constantly tired and worried about providing enough nutritious food for her family. She lives in a remote community and works part-time at the local school. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her BMI is 31 kg/m2. Her children appear small for their age but are otherwise well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDuring the consultation, she mentions that many families in her community struggle to access affordable, healthy food options. The nearest supermarket is over 100 km away, and the local store has limited fresh produce at high prices.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following social determinants of health is most directly addressed by establishing a community-led fruit and vegetable garden?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Education","Employment","Food security","Housing","Healthcare access"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis scenario highlights several social determinants of health affecting Indigenous communities, particularly in remote areas. The establishment of a community-led fruit and vegetable garden most directly addresses \u003Cstrong\u003Efood security\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a critical social determinant of health.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFood security\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the availability of and access to sufficient, safe, and nutritious food to meet dietary needs and food preferences for an active and healthy life. In this scenario, the community faces significant challenges in accessing affordable, healthy food options due to geographical isolation and limited local resources. A community garden directly improves food security by providing a local source of fresh, nutritious produce.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEducation\u003C/strong\u003E is an important social determinant of health, but it is not the primary focus of a community garden initiative. While the garden may provide educational opportunities about nutrition and agriculture, its main purpose is to address food availability and access.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmployment\u003C/strong\u003E can be indirectly affected by a community garden project, potentially creating some local job opportunities. However, addressing unemployment is not the primary goal of this initiative.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHousing\u003C/strong\u003E is a crucial social determinant of health, particularly in Indigenous communities where overcrowding and poor housing conditions are common issues. However, a community garden project does not directly address housing concerns.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHealthcare access\u003C/strong\u003E is another vital social determinant of health, especially in remote communities where medical facilities may be limited. While improved nutrition from a community garden may have positive health impacts, the garden itself does not directly address healthcare access issues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBy focusing on food security, a community-led fruit and vegetable garden addresses a fundamental social determinant of health. It provides a sustainable solution to improve access to nutritious food, which can have far-reaching effects on the overall health and wellbeing of community members. This approach also aligns with principles of community empowerment and self-determination, which are crucial in addressing health inequities in Indigenous populations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Food insecurity is a significant issue in many Indigenous communities, particularly in remote areas.","Community-led initiatives are often the most effective in addressing food security issues in Indigenous populations.","Addressing food insecurity requires a multifaceted approach that considers cultural, economic, and environmental factors.","Social determinants of health, such as access to nutritious food, significantly impact health outcomes in Indigenous communities."],"references":["Australian Institute of Health and Welfare. (n.d.). Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Health Performance Framework: 2.08 Income. Australian Government. https://www.indigenoushpf.gov.au/measures/2-08-income","National Aboriginal Community Controlled Health Organisation. (2022, December). Submission to the House of Representatives Standing Committee on Agriculture inquiry into food security in Australia. https://www.naccho.org.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85236"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14213"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85236","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85236"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-15T12:49:41+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-15T14:44:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6899"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102753"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"